    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09125"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1790-08-31">1790 г. августа 31.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Приказано <orgName ref="orgs.xml#orph01">воспитательного дома</orgName> попечителям разсмотреть и разобрать дело <persName ref="people.xml#kir02">Киршбаума</persName> с <persName ref="people.xml#bet01">Иоанном I. Бецким</persName>. <rs ref="people.xml#bet01">Сей</rs> ныне пишет и присылает непрестанно ко мне, говоря, что остается дело без разсмотрения, а <orgName ref="orgs.xml#orph01">дом воспитательный</orgName> без попечения. Осведомьтесь, в каком положении то дело.
                <note type="editorial">
                    Catherine writes about an affair between <persName ref="people.xml#bet01">I.I. Betskoi</persName> and <persName ref="people.xml#kir02">E.A. Kirshbaum</persName>. In 1790 as the regents of <orgName ref="orgs.xml#orph01">the Saint-Petersburg's Orphanage</orgName> departed to <name type="event" ref="events.xml#swedi02">the Russo-Swedish war</name>, Betskoi decided to regain the control over the orphanage and on <date when-custom="1790-06-04">June 4 1790</date> fired Kirshbaum, who was the orphanage's director at the time, alluding to his problems with health, and ordered to remove him by force on <date when-custom="1790-06-10">June 10 1790</date>, after Kirshbaum refused to leave the orphanage. Betskoi assumed that Kirshbaum would not make this affair go public, but the later made a complaint to Catherine about his unfair dismissal. Catherine addressed to the regents to decide on this affair and after the trial that was held on <date when-custom="1790-09-02">September 2 1790</date> took part of the fired employees of the orphanage. However, Catherine assumed that Kirshbaum could not keep holding his office in the orphanage and assigned him to <orgName ref="orgs.xml#cabi01">the Imperial Cabinet</orgName> ( 
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#opekun01">Opekuny Peterburgskogo vospitatel'nogo doma v tsarstvovanie Ekateriny 2</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 70-71.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                </note></p>
